// Create a gateway endpoint that returns whatever microsoft.com returns forwarding whatever arguments it is given | Hyperlambda gateway endpoint forwarding arguments | Hyperlambda endpoint serving as gateway endpoint to another endpoint with arguments | API gateway in Hyperlambda taking arguments
.arguments:*
add:x:../*/http.post/*/payload
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
http.post:"https://microsoft.com"
   convert:true
   payload
return-nodes:x:@http.get/*/content/*
